    {
        "content": "<p>Does anyone have a proof that pi is irrational on hand, that they could PR?</p>\n<p>I know that there is a PR in process <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6718\">#6718</a>, containing the much stronger result that it is transcendental, but there may be a way to go before that is merged.</p>\n<p>It feels a little embarrassing at this point in time to still not have this in. :-)</p>",
        "id": 470617769,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1726495423
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The proof <a href=\"https://kconrad.math.uconn.edu/blurbs/analysis/irrational.pdf\">here</a> (Niven's proof) should be rather easy to formalize.</p>",
        "id": 470625783,
        "sender_full_name": "Riccardo Brasca",
        "timestamp": 1726496898
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wouldn't be surprised if someone did it already. (If anyone has thoughts on <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6718\">#6718</a>, do let me know <span aria-label=\"innocent\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f607\" role=\"img\" title=\"innocent\">:innocent:</span>)</p>",
        "id": 470634571,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1726498088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"246273\">@Bhavik Mehta</span>  had a lean 3 PR with this result, and perhaps a lean4 translation locally?</p>",
