    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/pi.20is.20irrational.3F/near/471196606\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"755238\">Lihong Zhi</span> is it you who is doing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(3)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> in Lean? Can you also do <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>? We already have <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(2)=\\pi^2/6</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/6</span></span></span></span> thanks to David Loeffler, so this would be enough.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes. my student <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"708643\">@ahhwuhu</span> (Junqi Liu) and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"252627\">@Jujian Zhang</span>  are proving <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(3)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is irrational in Lean.  It should be easy to adjust their proof to show  <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(2)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is irrational.  They will do it later.</p>",
        "id": 471241577,
        "sender_full_name": "Lihong Zhi",
        "timestamp": 1726660944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110087\">Kim Morrison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/pi.20is.20irrational.3F/near/471126581\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"246273\">Bhavik Mehta</span>, would you be able to translate <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib3/blob/irrational-pi/src/analysis/special_functions/trigonometric/pi.lean\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib3/blob/irrational-pi/src/analysis/special_functions/trigonometric/pi.lean</a> and PR it?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sure, I have a ported version lying around somewhere. I never really viewed it as high priority since people are working on generalised versions already, but I don't mind doing it. (Similarly I did <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ζ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mn>6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\zeta(2) = \\pi^2 / 6</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07378em;\">ζ</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0641em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/6</span></span></span></span> about four years ago, but never bothered upstreaming it because David's work gives a more general result!)</p>",
        "id": 471282752,
        "sender_full_name": "Bhavik Mehta",
        "timestamp": 1726672199
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(There's been some \"we have this stuff but Lean doesn't\" going around, and it seems easier to explain \"well actually it does, see Mathlib\", rather than \"well actually it does, see Bhavik's un-PR'd work on this branch of an archived repository\".)</p>",
        "id": 471369919,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1726704534
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we can have a bit of community effort to get</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>feat: Lindemann-Weierstrass Theorem <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6718\">#6718</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>into mathlib in the near future. <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"307953\">Ruben Van de Velde</span> already started <span aria-label=\"octopus\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f419\" role=\"img\" title=\"octopus\">:octopus:</span></p>",
        "id": 471416915,
